{"id":14,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":14,"title":"Chapter 11: Enos","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 11"],["h1","Enos"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p3"},"Enos was Jacob’s son. He kept the plates and wrote on them after his father died."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/jacob/7.27"},"Jacob 7:27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p5"},"One day Enos was hunting in the forest. He thought about his father’s teachings and wanted to be forgiven of his sins."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.3-4"},"Enos 1:3–4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p7"},"Enos knelt and prayed to God. He prayed all day and was still praying when night came."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.4"},"Enos 1:4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p9"},"God told Enos that because of his faith in Jesus Christ, his sins were forgiven."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.5,8"},"Enos 1:5, 8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p11"},"Enos then wanted the Lord to bless the Nephites. He prayed for them, and the Lord said he would bless them if they obeyed his commandments."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.9-10"},"Enos 1:9–10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p13"},"Enos also wanted the Lord to bless the Lamanites. He prayed with great faith, and the Lord promised to do what Enos asked him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.11-12"},"Enos 1:11–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p15"},"Even though the Lamanites fought the Nephites and tried to destroy their records, Enos prayed that they would become a righteous people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.13-14"},"Enos 1:13–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p17"},"Enos prayed that the records he had kept would be safe. The Lord promised that someday he would give the Lamanites the teachings that were on the records."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.16"},"Enos 1:16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p19"},"Enos preached to the Nephites. He wanted them to believe in God and keep the commandments."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.10,19"},"Enos 1:10, 19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p21"},"The Nephites tried to teach the gospel to the Lamanites, but they would not listen. The Lamanites hated the Nephites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.20"},"Enos 1:20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_014_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p23"},"Enos spent his life teaching people about Jesus and the gospel. He served God and loved him all his days."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-11-enos.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/enos/1.26-27"},"Enos 1:26–27"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
